100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 8, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing issues of international security and disarmament amid rising tensions in Europe. In Turkey, the government announced reforms aimed at modernizing the nation, while in the United States, the ongoing debate over Prohibition continued to stir public sentiment. Meanwhile, the British Empire faced challenges in India, where calls for independence gained momentum, signaling a shift in colonial dynamics.
